<font color="#FF0000">REUP FOR A 2ND TOUR? NUTS!</font><br>
<tt>Sat Aug  2 15:27:07 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
A second tour? You had to be nuts!<br><br>
They had an agonizing ritual of &quot;clearance&quot; before they would let you DEROS. Some beancounter's delight of a form where you were supposed to get initials all over the place, even the &quot;library&quot;(?), wherever that was. You could dummy all the signatures you wanted EXCEPT the medics (they wouldn't let you out of country if you had some pretty bad stuff), and the REUP Sergeant. <br><br>
There I was in Cu Chi, with only two days left, and some E-6 was lecturing me on the benefits of a reup and another tour! I was scared to death that I wouldn't make it out, I was hot, I was dirty, I was completely burned out, and depressed, right on the bottom. I can still hear the words of how I could make E-6 real fast, how I had the talents they needed, and all the rest of the bullshit. All of a sudden, in that dim and dusty hooch, it suddenly became very clear to me how utterly shabby was all of this, how I had been really f***** over, and although this guy was just doing his job, I would have blown him away if I were armed.<br>
All I could see was an endless line of dirty hooches for the rest of my life.<br><br>
Back in the States, I grabbed my money and plane tickets, pushed my way through the degenerate welcomming committee at Oakland, and here I am now.<br><br>
There was no way in hell I wanted to repeat that experience, even as down and depressed as I was. I still had a shred of self respect left. I didn't have to prove I could do it and survive again!
